description: On the west coast of Sweden, a 390-kilometer bike path winds along sandy beaches, pine forests and wheat fields. It goes all the way to Denmark, where the gates open to Hamlet's castle and a spectacular museum of modern art.
title: A Scandinavian cycling epic of trolls, saunas and forests

description: Numerous clashes between law enforcement and pro-independence forces occurred on Sunday night. The hospital is once again inaccessible, as it was at the start of the insurrection, which began six weeks ago now and seems to be spreading to the bush.
title: New Caledonia: New clashes triggered by detention of pro-independence activists in mainland France

description: Sociologist Dominique Schnapper analyzes how the principles of freedom and equality that underpin democracy can be turned against it, which can lead to a climate of hatred and transform adversaries into enemies.
title: Sociologist Dominique Schnapper: 'Today, the president provokes rejection in a way that weakens our institutions'
